{"title_page": "Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Vex Red]]\n| cover        = Start_with_a_Strong_and_Persistent_Desire.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = 4 March 2002 <ref name=\"DISC\">[https://www.discogs.com/Vex-Red-Start-With-A-Strong-And-Persistent-Desire/master/328740 \"Album Information\"], ''Discogs'', Retrieved on 10 September 2018.</ref>\n| recorded     = 2000-2001\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Alternative rock]]\n| length       = {{duration|m=50|s=54}} <ref name=\"AM\">[https://www.amazon.co.uk/Start-Strong-Persistent-Desire-Vex/dp/B00005UP03 \"Album Information 2\"], ''Amazon'', Retrieved on 10 September 2018.</ref>\n| label        = [[Virgin Records|I Am]]\n| producer     = [[Ross Robinson]] <ref name=\"ALL\">{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/vex-red-mn0000805415/biography |title=Vex Red Biography |website=AllMusic |accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>\n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Itch\n | single1date = 2001\n | single2     = Can't Smile\n | single2date = 18 February 2002\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire''''' is the debut album by English [[alternative rock]] band [[Vex Red]]. It was released on 4 March 2002 through [[Virgin Records|I Am]] records. The album charted at number 48 on the [[UK Albums Chart]] and also spent two weeks on the chart. Two singles were released from the album. \"Itch\" was released in 2001, followed by \"Can't Smile\" in 2002 which reached number 45 in the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"OC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/11318/vex-red/ |title=Vex Red Chart History |website=Official Charts |accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe album was produced by nu metal producer [[Ross Robinson]], who also signed the band to his [[Virgin Records]] imprint \"I Am\" in the early 2000s <ref name=\"Allmusic\">{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/vex-red-mn0000805415/biography |title=Vex Red Biography |website=AllMusic |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = \n| MC = \n| aggregate1 = [[Album of the Year (website)|Album of the Year]]\n| aggregate1score = 68/100<ref name=\"AY\">{{cite web |url=https://www.albumoftheyear.org/album/47648-vex-red-start-with-a-strong-and-persistent-desire.php |title=Vex Red Album of the Year Aggregate |website=Album of the Year |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[All Music]]'' <ref name=\"ALLM\">{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/start-with-a-strong-and-persistent-desire-mw0000222107|title=Start With a Strong and Persistent Desire Album Review |website=All Music |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1Score = {{rating|2.5|5}}\n| rev3 = ''[[The Guardian]]'' <ref name=\"TG\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2002/feb/08/shopping.artsfeatures2 |title=Vex Red Guardian Album Review |website=The Guardian |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3|5}}\n| rev4 = ''[[NME]]'' <ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/reviews-nme-6160 |title=Vex Red NME Album Review |website=Album of the Year |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|7|10}}\n| rev1score = \n| rev2 = ''[[Drowned in Sound]]'' <ref name=\"DIS\">{{cite web |url=http://drownedinsound.com/releases/2844/reviews/3189- |title=Vex Red Drowned in Sound Album Review |website=Drowned in Sound |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|9.2|10}}\n| rev5 = ''[[Ultimate Guitar]]'' <ref name=\"UG\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ultimate-guitar.com/reviews/compact_discs/vex_red/start_with_a_strong_and_persistent_desire/ |title=Vex Red Ultimate Guitar Album Review |website=Ultimate Guitar |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n| rev5Score = {{Rating|9|10}}\n}}\n\nCritical reception to the album was positive upon release. [[Drowned in Sound]] scored the album highly, reviewer Sajini Wijetilleka had particular praise for \"Can't Smile\", speaking of the track; \"Sequenced-synth loops, emotional vocals and energised guitar swirls give us the excellent \u2018Can\u2019t Smile\u2019, the best record that Gavin Rossdale wanted to, but could never ever make.\".<ref name=\"DIS\"/> [[NME]] reviewer April Long gave the album positive write up stating; \"The title says it all. Underpinning every spastic roar and raging riff on \nVex Red\u2018s debut is the burning desire to make something enormous, resonant and real.\".<ref name=\"NME\"/> [[The Guardian]] gave the album 3/5 stars summarizing about the bands potential; \" Vex Red take it a step further and become their own men. They might just evolve into greatness.\".<ref name=\"TG\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing  = Vex Red\n| total_length = 50:54\n| title1       = The Closest\n| length1      = 4:48\n| title2       = Dermo\n| length2      = 3:33\n| title3       = Can't Smile\n| length3      = 4:49\n| title4       = Untitled\n| length4      = 5:18\n| title5       = Itch\n| length5      = 3:47\n| title6       = Bully Me\n| length6      = 4:53\n| title7       = Cause and Solution\n| length7      = 4:27\n| title8       = Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire\n| length8      = 3:52\n| title9       = Clone Jesus\n| length9      = 4:36\n| title10      = Sleep does Nothing for you\n| length10     = 3:55\n| title11      = Vert\n| length11     = 6:56\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Vex Red'''\n* Terry Abbot \u2013 lead vocals, guitar\n* [[Ash Soan]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n* Ant Forbes \u2013 guitar, keyboards\n* Nick Goulding \u2013 bass guitar, guitar\n* Keith Lambert - bass guitar, programming\n\n{{col-2}}\n'''Production personnel'''\n* Ross Robinson \u2013 Producer\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2002)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|61|date=20020316|rowheader=true|accessdate=10 September 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK2|48|date=20020316|rowheader=true|accessdate=10 September 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UKRock|3|date=20020316|rowheader=true|accessdate=10 September 2018}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| Cat #\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 4 March 2002\n| rowspan=\"2\"| CD\n| rowspan=\"3\"| I Am\n| CDVUS 215, 7243 8 11798 2 6\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/Vex-Red-Start-With-A-Strong-And-Persistent-Desire/master/328740 |title=Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire \u2013 Album by Vex Red |website=Discogs |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Japan\n| VJCP-68421, 7243 8 11798 2 6\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/Vex-Red-Start-With-A-Strong-And-Persistent-Desire/master/328740 |title=Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire (Japan) \u2013 Album by Vex Red |website=Discogs |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Europe\n| rowspan=\"1\"| LP\n| 7243 8 11789 1\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/Vex-Red-Start-With-A-Strong-And-Persistent-Desire/master/328740 |title=Start with a Strong and Persistent Desire (Europe) \u2013 Album by Vex Red |website=Discogs |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2002 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=Sep