_and_Persistent_Desire"}
{"title_page": "Voiceserve", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=September 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name         = Voiceserve Inc.\n| logo         = \n| type         = Public\n| traded_as    = NASDAQ: VSRV\n| industry     = [[Telecommunications]] and [[Mobile network|Mobile]]\n| founded = December 9, 2005, \n| hq_location = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| key_people   = Michael Bibelman (CEO and Director)<br/> Alexander Ellinson (Chairman of Board of Directors, President)<br/> Krzysztof Oglaza (CTO) \n| products     = [[Mobile Dialers]]<br>\nEnhanced [[Rich Communication Services]]\n<br>iPhone, iPad, Android, Blackberry, and Windows [[Softphone]]<br>\nClass5 [[Softswitch]]\n| homepage     = {{URL|voiceserve.com}}{{dead link|date=May 2015}}\n}}\n\n'''Voiceserve Inc.''' is a [[Delaware]], USA [[telecommunications]] and [[softswitch]] company headquartered in [[Middlesex]], [[United Kingdom]] and incorporated December 9, 2005. The company offers its own in-house developed VoIP, mobility, and IP-PBX software solutions{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}} with management, administration, billing, mobility, hosted IP-PBX, and softphone functionality found among its services, VoipSwitch, Call-to-PBX, and Vippie.<ref name=\"Owen\">{{cite news|last=Owen|first=Jeff|title=Voiceserve offers complete VoIP/IP-PBX product line|url=http://www.telecomreseller.com/2011/11/02/voiceserve-offers-complete-voipip-pbx-product-line/|newspaper=Telecom Reseller|date=November 2, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===Background===\nThe co-founders of Voiceserve are Michael Bibelman (CEO) and Alexander Ellinson (Chairman of the Board of Directors and President). Mr. Bibelman began a marketing telecommunications career in 1994 as an independent reseller for calling card companies. In 1996 he joined Ambro International, known for the \"Big Talk\" calling card<ref name=\"VOICESERVE-INC-Mar-2011-10-K/A\">{{cite web|url=http://edgar.secdatabase.com/2342/121390011001066/filing-main.htm |title=VOICESERVE INC, Form 10-K/A, ITEM 10.   DIRECTORS, EXECUTIVE OFFICERS, PROMOTERS AND CORPORATE GOVERNANCE, Filing Date Mar 1, 2011 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =May 15, 2018}}</ref>  and contributed by introducing them to the United Kingdom and Scotland telecommunications market. Mr. Ellinson began a career in telecommunications in 1994 as an independent marketing agent for a European telecommunications provider and contributed by closing major contracts with large enterprises in the Netherlands and Germany. In 1996, he also became involved in Ambro International.<ref>{{cite web|title=Voiceserve IncVSRV:QB|url=http://markets.ft.com/research/Markets/Tearsheets/Directors-and-dealings?s=VSRV:QBB|publisher=Financial Times|accessdate=25 February 2013|date=February 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nMr. Krzysztof Oglaza is the chief technical officer of VoipSwitch which Voiceserve acquired in 2008. He completed an engineering degree in information technology at the Politeck School Opole in Poland and later a master's degree in technology in 2000. Next, he became a partner in Intermik S.C., a Polish Internet service provider. In 2002, Intermik was incorporated by [[Netia]] Holding.<ref>{{cite web|last=Siebielski |first=Robert |title=Netia poprzez Internetia Telekom kupuje firm\u0119 Intermik |url=http://www.operatorzy.pl/historia_rynku_telekomunikacyjnego;hst=1711754523 |publisher=OperatorZYPL |accessdate=25 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202222113/http://www.operatorzy.pl/historia_rynku_telekomunikacyjnego%3Bhst%3D1711754523 |archivedate=2 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> Mr. Oglaza was the co-founding director of VoipSwitch in 2001.\n\n===Time Line===\n* December 9, 2005 Voiceserve incorporated in Delaware, USA.<ref name=\"VOICESERVE-INC-Mar-2011-10-K/A\"/> \n* February 14, 2007 OTC Bulletin Board listing (VSRV) <ref>{{cite web|title=OTCBB Profile for VSRV|url=http://www.otcbb.com/profiles/VSRV.htm|publisher=OTCBB|accessdate=21 February 2013}}</ref> \n* 2008 Voiceserve acquired VoipSwitch.<ref name=\"VOICESERVE-INC-Sep-2010-S-1\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/769/0001213900-10-003825.pdf |title=VOICESERVE INC, Form S-1, Filing Date Sep 17, 2010 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =May 15, 2018}}</ref> \n* March 31, 2009 Voiceserve began mobile license sales.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voiceserve Reports Preliminary Fourth Quarter Results|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Voiceserve+Reports+Preliminary+Fourth+Quarter+Results.-a0196962014|newspaper=The Free Library|date=March 31, 2009}}</ref>\n*2010  Voiceserve launched retail business and introduced VOD (video on demand).<ref>{{cite web|title=Voiceserve, Inc. Reports Full Year and Fourth Quarter Fiscal 2011 Financial Results|url=http://www.faqs.org/sec-filings/110706/VOICESERVE-INC_8-K/f8k070511ex99i_vserve.htm|publisher=FAQS.org|accessdate=22 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=VoIPSWITCH Adds Video over IP Component |url=http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/23/voipswitch-adds-video-over-ip-component/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130411220337/http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/23/voipswitch-adds-video-over-ip-component/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 11, 2013 |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=December 23, 2009 }}</ref> \n* 2011 In Q1, enterprise sales launched and two carrier contracts were signed, one in Saudi Arabia and the other in United Arab Emirates.<ref>{{cite web|last=Zappulla|first=Yvonne|title=VOICESERVE INC - FORM 8-K - EX-99.2 - TRANSCRIPT OF VOICESERVE?S EARNINGS CALL - August 24, 2011|url=http://www.faqs.org/sec-filings/110824/VOICESERVE-INC_8-K/f8k081511ex99ii_voiceserve.htm|accessdate=22 February 2013}}</ref> \n* September 2011 Voiceserve completed its first joint venture with Dialogic.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dialogic Inc. And Voiceserve Inc Collaborate on Mobile Video Conferencing Solution|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/DLGC.O/key-developments/article/2396082|newspaper=Reuters News|date=September 6, 2011}}</ref> \n* 2012 Voiceserve launched cloud-based VoIP PBX Direct to Consumers and Small Businesses.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voiceserve Launches Cloud-Based VoIP PBX Product to Consumers and Small Businesses Through Its CalltoPBX.com Website|url=http://mw.newsblaze.com/story/2012010405004400023.mwir/topstory.html|newspaper=News Blaze|date=January 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Products and Services==\n\n===Smart Phone Dialers===\n\nSmart phone dialers describes the VoipSwitch [[softphone]]s. They are multi-functional [[VoIP]] applications for PCs and all mobile platforms. The software is a solution{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}}  for established telecommunications providers and for new VoIP (voice over Internet protocol) businesses. They can be integrated with any Class 5 or IMS platform including VoipSwitch itself. VoipSwitch engineers assist with implementation of mobile and PC softphones. The softphones include video and voice communications and recording, content sharing, provisioning, social network integration, voice mail, users discovery, and social profile information. The service is ready to white label with provider's specific logo and design.\n\nThe smart phone dialer softphones have versions compatible with [[iPhone]] and iPad, Android, [[BlackBerry]], [[Symbian]] and Windows.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=Solaiemes\u2019 Juan Mateu Among Many Innovators at GSMA Mobile World Congress |url=http://www.techistan.com/2010/02/08/solaiemes-juan-mateu-among-many-innovators-at-gsma-mobile-world-congress/ |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=February 8, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411215902/http://www.techistan.com/2010/02/08/solaiemes-juan-mateu-among-many-innovators-at-gsma-mobile-world-congress/ |archivedate=11 April 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=Apple AppStore Allows SIP Clients on WiFi, 3G and Edge Connections |url=http://www.techistan.com/2010/03/19/apple-appstore-allows-sip-clients-on-wifi-3g-and-edge-connections/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130411215431/http://www.techistan.com/2010/03/19/apple-appstore-allows-sip-clients-on-wifi-3g-and-edge-connections/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 11, 2013 |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=March 19, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=Symbian Nokia Dialer with Low-bandwidth Consumption |url=http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/28/symbian-nokia-dialer-with-low-bandwidth-consumption/ |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=December 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411222224/http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/28/symbian-nokia-dialer-with-low-bandwidth-consumption/ |archivedate=11 April 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Enhanced Rich Communications===\n\nThe Enhanced Rich Communications Suite are the mobile eRCS dialers of iPhone and Android with server side software solution.<ref>{{cite news|last=Raju|first=Shanbhag|title=Voiceserve to Introduce its Latest Voipswitch eRCS Mobile Applications|url=http://voip-routers.tmcnet.com/topics/voip-routers/articles/294453-voiceserve-introduce-its-latest-voipswitch-ercs-mobile-applications.htm|accessdate=25 February 2013|newspaper=TMCnet|date=June 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===VoipSwitch Class5 Softswitch===\n\nVoipSwitch is a software platform that enables VoIP services roll-out. It contains the necessary elements required in successful implementation of various VoIP (voice over Internet protocol) services. Features include follow-me, call forwarding, voice mail, video support, web call shop interface, web self-care portal for end-users and support, online payments, mobile SIP, and call recording. It can include a calling card platform with IP IVR including pin and pinless ([[telephone card]]) scenarios, callback solution{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}}  with trigger type methods of SMS, missed call, and web [[callback (telecommunications)]]. The [[softswitch]] has SMS features for wholesale and retail services that use [[HTTP]], SIP [[session initiation protocol]] and [[Short Message Peer-to-Peer|SMPP]] protocols. Its Windows communicator has instant messaging, SMS, voice mail and other modules. Its multi-tenant, multi-user IP PBX platform offers hosted services. Other features include unified messaging, voice mail/SMS forwarding to SMS or email, and voice mail transcriptions. Its instant messenger functionality has XMPP protocol support, presence, chat, and file transfer.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sandstrom |first=Peter |title=Contact Support Customer/Reseller TotalView Login HomeBusiness Connect PricingPartnersTechnologyAbout Us Confirmed BandTel Interoperable High Volume Telcom Switching: VoIPSwitch |url=http://www.bandtel.com/confirmed-bandtel-interoperable-high-volume-telcom-switching-partners-voipswitch.html |publisher=Bandtel |accessdate=25 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209213533/http://www.bandtel.com/confirmed-bandtel-interoperable-high-volume-telcom-switching-partners-voipswitch.html |archivedate=9 December 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Awards, Membership, and other Recognition==\n* Voiceserve's Voipswitch Vippie mobile SIP softphone obtained the 2009 Unified Communications TMC Labs Award.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gray|first=Tim|title=Voiceserve's Voipswitch Vippie Mobile SIP Softphone Lands 2009 UC TMC Labs Award|url=http://www.tmcnet.com/channels/voipswitch/articles/57340-voiceserves-voipswitch-vippie-mobile-sip-softphone-lands-2009.htm|newspaper=TMC|date=June 4, 2009}}</ref> \n* Voiceserve presented at International Telecoms Week, Seoul, Korea, in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voiceserve Presents At The International Telecoms Week 2010 In Washington DC And The World IT Show In Seoul, Korea |url=http://www.thestreet.com/story/10766144/voiceserve-presents-at-the-international-telecoms-week-2010-in-washington-dc-and-the-world-it-show-in-seoul-korea.html |newspaper=The Street |date=May 25, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010222440/http://www.thestreet.com/story/10766144/voiceserve-presents-at-the-international-telecoms-week-2010-in-washington-dc-and-the-world-it-show-in-seoul-korea.html |archivedate=October 10, 2012 |df= }}</ref> \n* VoipSwitch VOD (video on demand) won the 2011 TMC IPTV Excellence Award.<ref name=\"Owen\"/> \n* On August 27, 2011, DIDX co-founder and VoIP podcaster interviewed Voiceserve co-founder Michael Bibelman.<ref>{{cite news|title=VoipSwitch CEO Michael Bibelman 14K Deployments|url=http://www.podcast-directory.co.uk/episodes/voipswitch-ceo-michael-bibelman-14k-deployments-11387215.html|newspaper=Podcast-Directory UK|date=August 27, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Bowen|first=Suzanne|title=VoipSwitch CEO Michael Bibelman 14K Deployments|newspaper=http://www.didx.net/podcast/?p=episode&name=2009-12-17_michaelbibelman.mp3|date=August 22, 2011}}</ref> \n* ''Tech Talk with Craig Peterson'' interviewed VoipSwitch/Vippie CEO Alexander Ellison on November 22, 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last=Peterson|first=Craig|title=TTWCP-686-02-alexander_ellinson-voipswitch-vippie|url=http://podcast.tech-talk-with-craig-peterson.com/index.php?id=2625|newspaper=Tech Talk with Craig Peterson Podcast|date=November 22, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:VoIP companies of the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=September 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name         = Voiceserve Inc.\n| logo         = \n| type         = Public\n| traded_as    = NASDAQ: VSRV\n| industry     = [[Telecommunications]] and [[Mobile network|Mobile]]\n| founded = December 9, 2005, \n| hq_location = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| key_people   = Michael Bibelman (CEO and Director)<br/> Alexander Ellinson (Chairman of Board of Directors, President)<br/> Krzysztof Oglaza (CTO) \n| products     = [[Mobile Dialers]]<br>\nEnhanced [[Rich Communication Services]]\n<br>iPhone, iPad, Android, Blackberry, and Windows [[Softphone]]<br>\nClass5 [[Softswitch]]\n| homepage     = {{URL|voiceserve.com}}{{dead link|date=May 2015}}\n}}\n\n'''Voiceserve Inc.''' is a [[Delaware]], USA [[telecommunications]] and [[softswitch]] company headquartered in [[Middlesex]], [[United Kingdom]] and incorporated December 9, 2005. The company offers its own in-house developed VoIP, mobility, and IP-PBX software solutions{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}} with management, administration, billing, mobility, hosted IP-PBX, and softphone functionality found among its services, VoipSwitch, Call-to-PBX, and Vippie.<ref name=\"Owen\">{{cite news|last=Owen|first=Jeff|title=Voiceserve offers complete VoIP/IP-PBX product line|url=http://www.telecomreseller.com/2011/11/02/voiceserve-offers-complete-voipip-pbx-product-line/|newspaper=Telecom Reseller|date=November 2, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===Background===\nThe co-founders of Voiceserve are Michael Bibelman (CEO) and Alexander Ellinson (Chairman of the Board of Directors and President). Mr. Bibelman began a marketing telecommunications career in 1994 as an independent reseller for calling card companies. In 1996 he joined Ambro International, known for the \"Big Talk\" calling card<ref name=\"VOICESERVE-INC-Mar-2011-10-K/A\">{{cite web|url=http://edgar.secdatabase.com/2342/121390011001066/filing-main.htm |title=VOICESERVE INC, Form 10-K/A, ITEM 10.   DIRECTORS, EXECUTIVE OFFICERS, PROMOTERS AND CORPORATE GOVERNANCE, Filing Date Mar 1, 2011 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =May 15, 2018}}</ref>  and contributed by introducing them to the United Kingdom and Scotland telecommunications market. Mr. Ellinson began a career in telecommunications in 1994 as an independent marketing agent for a European telecommunications provider and contributed by closing major contracts with large enterprises in the Netherlands and Germany. In 1996, he also became involved in Ambro International.<ref>{{cite web|title=Voiceserve IncVSRV:QB|url=http://markets.ft.com/research/Markets/Tearsheets/Directors-and-dealings?s=VSRV:QBB|publisher=Financial Times|accessdate=25 February 2013|date=February 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nMr. Krzysztof Oglaza is the chief technical officer of VoipSwitch which Voiceserve acquired in 2008. He completed an engineering degree in information technology at the Politeck School Opole in Poland and later a master's degree in technology in 2000. Next, he became a partner in Intermik S.C., a Polish Internet service provider. In 2002, Intermik was incorporated by [[Netia]] Holding.<ref>{{cite web|last=Siebielski |first=Robert |title=Netia poprzez Internetia Telekom kupuje firm\u0119 Intermik |url=http://www.operatorzy.pl/historia_rynku_telekomunikacyjnego;hst=1711754523 |publisher=OperatorZYPL |accessdate=25 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202222113/http://www.operatorzy.pl/historia_rynku_telekomunikacyjnego%3Bhst%3D1711754523 |archivedate=2 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> Mr. Oglaza was the co-founding director of VoipSwitch in 2001.\n\n===Time Line===\n* December 9, 2005 Voiceserve incorporated in Delaware, USA.<ref name=\"VOICESERVE-INC-Mar-2011-10-K/A\"/> \n* February 14, 2007 OTC Bulletin Board listing (VSRV) <ref>{{cite web|title=OTCBB Profile for VSRV|url=http://www.otcbb.com/profiles/VSRV.htm|publisher=OTCBB|accessdate=21 February 2013}}</ref> \n* 2008 Voiceserve acquired VoipSwitch.<ref name=\"VOICESERVE-INC-Sep-2010-S-1\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/769/0001213900-10-003825.pdf |title=VOICESERVE INC, Form S-1, Filing Date Sep 17, 2010 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =May 15, 2018}}</ref> \n* March 31, 2009 Voiceserve began mobile license sales.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voiceserve Reports Preliminary Fourth Quarter Results|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Voiceserve+Reports+Preliminary+Fourth+Quarter+Results.-a0196962014|newspaper=The Free Library|date=March 31, 2009}}</ref>\n*2010  Voiceserve launched retail business and introduced VOD (video on demand).<ref>{{cite web|title=Voiceserve, Inc. Reports Full Year and Fourth Quarter Fiscal 2011 Financial Results|url=http://www.faqs.org/sec-filings/110706/VOICESERVE-INC_8-K/f8k070511ex99i_vserve.htm|publisher=FAQS.org|accessdate=22 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=VoIPSWITCH Adds Video over IP Component |url=http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/23/voipswitch-adds-video-over-ip-component/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130411220337/http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/23/voipswitch-adds-video-over-ip-component/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 11, 2013 |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=December 23, 2009 }}</ref> \n* 2011 In Q1, enterprise sales launched and two carrier contracts were signed, one in Saudi Arabia and the other in United Arab Emirates.<ref>{{cite web|last=Zappulla|first=Yvonne|title=VOICESERVE INC - FORM 8-K - EX-99.2 - TRANSCRIPT OF VOICESERVE?S EARNINGS CALL - August 24, 2011|url=http://www.faqs.org/sec-filings/110824/VOICESERVE-INC_8-K/f8k081511ex99ii_voiceserve.htm|accessdate=22 February 2013}}</ref> \n* September 2011 Voiceserve completed its first joint venture with Dialogic.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dialogic Inc. And Voiceserve Inc Collaborate on Mobile Video Conferencing Solution|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/DLGC.O/key-developments/article/2396082|newspaper=Reuters News|date=September 6, 2011}}</ref> \n* 2012 Voiceserve launched cloud-based VoIP PBX Direct to Consumers and Small Businesses.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voiceserve Launches Cloud-Based VoIP PBX Product to Consumers and Small Businesses Through Its CalltoPBX.com Website|url=http://mw.newsblaze.com/story/2012010405004400023.mwir/topstory.html|newspaper=News Blaze|date=January 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Products and Services==\n\n===Smart Phone Dialers===\n\nSmart phone dialers describes the VoipSwitch [[softphone]]s. They are multi-functional [[VoIP]] applications for PCs and all mobile platforms. The software is a solution{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}}  for established telecommunications providers and for new VoIP (voice over Internet protocol) businesses. They can be integrated with any Class 5 or IMS platform including VoipSwitch itself. VoipSwitch engineers assist with implementation of mobile and PC softphones. The softphones include video and voice communications and recording, content sharing, provisioning, social network integration, voice mail, users discovery, and social profile information. The service is ready to white label with provider's specific logo and design.\n\nThe smart phone dialer softphones have versions compatible with [[iPhone]] and iPad, Android, [[BlackBerry]], [[Symbian]] and Windows.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=Solaiemes\u2019 Juan Mateu Among Many Innovators at GSMA Mobile World Congress |url=http://www.techistan.com/2010/02/08/solaiemes-juan-mateu-among-many-innovators-at-gsma-mobile-world-congress/ |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=February 8, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411215902/http://www.techistan.com/2010/02/08/solaiemes-juan-mateu-among-many-innovators-at-gsma-mobile-world-congress/ |archivedate=11 April 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=Apple AppStore Allows SIP Clients on WiFi, 3G and Edge Connections |url=http://www.techistan.com/2010/03/19/apple-appstore-allows-sip-clients-on-wifi-3g-and-edge-connections/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130411215431/http://www.techistan.com/2010/03/19/apple-appstore-allows-sip-clients-on-wifi-3g-and-edge-connections/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 11, 2013 |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=March 19, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh |first=Omar |title=Symbian Nokia Dialer with Low-bandwidth Consumption |url=http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/28/symbian-nokia-dialer-with-low-bandwidth-consumption/ |accessdate=25 February 2013 |newspaper=Techistan |date=December 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411222224/http://www.techistan.com/2009/12/28/symbian-nokia-dialer-with-low-bandwidth-consumption/ |archivedate=11 April 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Enhanced Rich Communications===\n\nThe Enhanced Rich Communications Suite are the mobile eRCS dialers of iPhone and Android with server side software solution.<ref>{{cite news|last=Raju|first=Shanbhag|title=Voiceserve to Introduce its Latest Voipswitch eRCS Mobile Applications|url=http://voip-routers.tmcnet.com/topics/voip-routers/articles/294453-voiceserve-introduce-its-latest-voipswitch-ercs-mobile-applications.htm|accessdate=25 February 2013|newspaper=TMCnet|date=June 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===VoipSwitch Class5 Softswitch===\n\nVoipSwitch is a software platform that enables VoIP services roll-out. It contains the necessary elements required in successful implementation of various VoIP (voice over Internet protocol) services. Features include follow-me, call forwarding, voice mail, video support, web call shop interface, web self-care portal for end-users and support, online payments, mobile SIP, and call recording. It can include a calling card platform with IP IVR including pin and pinless ([[telephone card]]) scenarios, callback solution{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}}  with trigger type methods of SMS, missed call, and web [[callback (telecommunications)]]. The [[softswitch]] has SMS features for wholesale and retail services that use [[HTTP]], SIP [[session initiation protocol]] and [[SMPP]] protocols. Its Windows communicator has instant messaging, SMS, voice mail and other modules. Its multi-tenant, multi-user IP PBX platform offers hosted services. Other features include unified messaging, voice mail/SMS forwarding to SMS or email, and voice mail transcriptions. Its instant messenger functionality has XMPP protocol support, presence, chat, and file transfer.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sandstrom |first=Peter |title=Contact Support Customer/Reseller TotalView Login HomeBusiness Connect PricingPartnersTechnologyAbout Us Confirmed BandTel Interoperable High Volume Telcom Switching: VoIPSwitch |url=http://www.bandtel.com/confirmed-bandtel-interoperable-high-volume-telcom-switching-partners-voipswitch.html |publisher=Bandtel |accessdate=25 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209213533/http://www.bandtel.com/confirmed-bandtel-interoperable-high-volume-telcom-switching-partners-voipswitch.html |archivedate=9 December 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Awards, Membership, and other Recognition==\n* Voiceserve's Voipswitch Vippie mobile SIP softphone obtained the 2009 Unified Communications TMC Labs Award.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gray|first=Tim|title=Voiceserve's Voipswitch Vippie Mobile SIP Softphone Lands 2009 UC TMC Labs Award|url=http://www.tmcnet.com/channels/voipswitch/articles/57340-voiceserves-voipswitch-vippie-mobile-sip-softphone-lands-2009.htm|newspaper=TMC|date=June 4, 2009}}</ref> \n* Voiceserve presented at International Telecoms Week, Seoul, Korea, in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=Voiceserve Presents At The International Telecoms Week 2010 In Washington DC And The World IT Show In Seoul, Korea |url=http://www.thestreet.com/story/10766144/voiceserve-presents-at-the-international-telecoms-week-2010-in-washington-dc-and-the-world-it-show-in-seoul-korea.html |newspaper=The Street |date=May 25, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010222440/http://www.thestreet.com/story/10766144/voiceserve-presents-at-the-international-telecoms-week-2010-in-washington-dc-and-the-world-it-show-in-seoul-korea.html |archivedate=October 10, 2012 |df= }}</ref> \n* VoipSwitch VOD (video on demand) won the 2011 TMC IPTV Excellence Award.<ref name=\"Owen\"/> \n* On August 27, 2011, DIDX co-founder and VoIP podcaster interviewed Voiceserve co-founder Michael Bibelman.<ref>{{cite news|title=VoipSwitch CEO Michael Bibelman 14K Deployments|url=http://www.podcast-directo